{"questionId":"27759","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>9</mn></math>, let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Π</mi></math>&nbsp;be the plane containing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the coordinates of the point on the plane&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Π</mi></math>&nbsp;which is closest to the origin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find the equation of the line through&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;perpendicular to the plane&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>t</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find the point where the line and plane intersect&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>t</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find the point where the line and plane intersect&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>so the point on the plane closest to the origin is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>choose a point on the plane <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p>\n<p>distance to the origin is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>since <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> is independent of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>, distance is minimised when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(R1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> for which their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp;is minimised&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>so the point on the plane closest to the origin is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find a vector from the origin to the closest point on the plane&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>t</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>distance to the origin&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msqrt><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>check in equation of plane&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;to get&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(R1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>t</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>distance to the origin&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msqrt><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>check in equation of plane&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;to get&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(R1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>so the point on the plane closest to the origin is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27759","referenceCode":"22N.2.AHL.TZ0.12d.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the coordinates of the point on the plane Π which is closest to the origin 0, 0, 0.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Vector equation of line","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Quadratic function"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}